<Event
kind="Panel"
name="It's not the Length, it's the Mirth: Game Length Versus Value"
location="Wyvern"
    datetime="03/13/2011 16:30:00"
    end="03/13/2011 17:30:00"
	description="With new forms of distribution for video games come new pricing models. Outlets like Apple's iOS App Store and digital distribution storefronts like Xbox Live Arcade and PSN are challenging the convention of $60 AAA retail titles, and complicating the already peculiar brand of calculus that gamers use when determining 'value'. Why is $1 okay on iPhone but $6 is too expensive? Why is one ten-hour retail game criticized for being 'too short' while others aren't? Why are we so hung up on game length? Join Christopher Grant (editor-in-chief, Joystiq.com) and panelists as they wrestle with this age-old quandary."
/>

